<tbody>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Subject</th>
<td colspan="3">Urgency to Tackle the Problems of Low Birthrate Highlighted at the Population Day Ceremony</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Date</th>
<td>2014-07-17</td>
<th scope="row">Hit</th>
<td>5015</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Contents</th>
<td class="view" colspan="3"><p align="center" class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: center; margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt">
<b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><u><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt"><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000">Urgency to Tackle the Problems of Low Birthrate Highlighted at the Population Day Ceremony <o:p></o:p></font></font></span></u></b></p>
<p class="MsoListParagraph" style="text-indent: -18pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt 56pt; mso-para-margin-left: 0gd; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1">
<font color="#000000"><font face="Times New Roman"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'times new roman'"><span style="mso-list: ignore">-<span style="font: 7pt 'times new roman'">          </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt">Government hosts events, including a symposium on population education and awards men of merits on the 3rd Population Day – <o:p></o:p></span></font></font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt">
<span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt"><o:p><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman"> </font></o:p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt">
<span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt"><font color="#000000"><font face="Times New Roman">The Ministry of Health and Welfare hosts ‘the 3<sup>rd</sup> Population Day’ ceremony beginning 14:00 on July 11, 2014 at the aT Center in Yangjaedong, Seoul. <o:p></o:p></font></font></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent: -8.8pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt 8.8pt; mso-char-indent-count: -.8; tab-stops: 7.1pt">
<span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 11pt"><font color="#000000"><font face="Times New Roman">* In 2012, the government established ‘population day,’ which falls on the same day of the world population day (July 11) in order to raise the awareness of population issues and to aggressively tackle problems of low birthrate and aging population. <o:p></o:p></font></font></span></p>
<p class="MsoListParagraph" style="text-indent: -18pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt 14.2pt; mso-para-margin-left: 0gd; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: 0cm">
<font color="#000000"><font face="Times New Roman"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'times new roman'"><span style="mso-list: ignore">-</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt">The population day ceremony, which will be attended by 300 representatives from the national assembly, central and local governments, businesses and civic groups, will be held to call the public attention on addressing population issues especially since Korea is one of the OCED member countries whose total fertility rate is low although the Korean government made strong efforts to raise the birthrate in the past decade. <o:p></o:p></span></font></font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent: -9.6pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt 9.6pt; mso-char-indent-count: -.8; tab-stops: 7.1pt">
<span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt"><o:p><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman"> </font></o:p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; tab-stops: 0cm">
<span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt"><font color="#000000"><font face="Times New Roman">At the ceremony, the government will give awards to 46 organizations and individuals in recognition of their contribution for pro-natal policies, and promoting the balance between work and family life <o:p></o:p></font></font></span></p>
<p class="MsoListParagraph" style="text-indent: -18pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt 21.3pt; mso-para-margin-left: 0gd; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: 0cm">
<font face="Times New Roman"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; color: black; font-size: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'times new roman'"><span style="mso-list: ignore">-<span style="font: 7pt 'times new roman'">          </span></span></span><font color="#000000"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt">Kyungnam Bank President Sohn Kyo-deok will be awarded a Moran Medal for his contribution to address long-work hours and to reflect the degree of efforts made by departments and department heads to promote work-family life balance in performance metrics. <span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> </span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; background: white; color: black; font-size: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: µ¸¿ò"><o:p></o:p></span></font></font></p>
<p class="MsoListParagraph" style="text-indent: -18pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt 21.3pt; mso-para-margin-left: 0gd; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: 0cm">
<font face="Times New Roman"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; color: black; font-size: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'times new roman'"><span style="mso-list: ignore">-<span style="font: 7pt 'times new roman'">          </span></span></span><font color="#000000"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt">BB Tech CEO Sung Yeul-hak will receive a Mongnyeon Medal, in recognition of his commitment to setting up a department dedicated to promote work-family life balance and to implement flexible work hours. </span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; background: white; color: black; font-size: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: µ¸¿ò"><o:p></o:p></span></font></font></p>
<p class="MsoListParagraph" style="text-indent: -18pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt 21.3pt; mso-para-margin-left: 0gd; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: 0cm">
<font face="Times New Roman"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; color: black; font-size: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'times new roman'"><span style="mso-list: ignore">-<span style="font: 7pt 'times new roman'">          </span></span></span><font color="#000000"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt">The government will also award </span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; background: white; color: black; font-size: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: µ¸¿ò">a Civil Merit Medal</span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt"> to </span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; background: white; color: black; font-size: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: µ¸¿ò">Lee Sam-sik</span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt">, a research analyst at the Korea Institute for Health and Social Affairs</span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; background: white; color: black; font-size: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: µ¸¿ò">, and a Service Merit Meal to Professor Cha Woo-kyoo of Korea National University of Education in recognition of their hard work on policy studies to address low birthrate and for promoting population education to enhance public awareness. <o:p></o:p></span></font></font></p>
<p class="MsoListParagraph" style="text-indent: -18pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt 21.3pt; mso-para-margin-left: 0gd; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: 0cm">
<font face="Times New Roman"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; color: black; font-size: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'times new roman'"><span style="mso-list: ignore">-<span style="font: 7pt 'times new roman'">          </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; background: white; color: black; font-size: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: µ¸¿ò">In addition, Yoo Young-kwon, Public Health Center Chief in Sacheon City will receive a Civil Merit Medal for his leadership in promoting pro-natal culture in the region through close collaboration with the military, academics and the local government. <span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> </span><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent: -12pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt 12pt; mso-char-indent-count: -1.0; tab-stops: 14.2pt">
<span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; background: white; color: black; font-size: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: µ¸¿ò"><o:p><font face="Times New Roman"> </font></o:p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt; tab-stops: 0cm">
<span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; background: white; color: black; font-size: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: µ¸¿ò"><font face="Times New Roman">The government will grant awards and prizes (Award from the Minister of Health and Welfare, cash prize) to individuals whose work stood out among others in Birthrate Improving Idea Competition, Pro-natal Slogan Competition, Pro-natal UCC competition, and other events held to celebrate the population day.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span><o:p></o:p></font></span></p>
<p class="MsoListParagraph" style="text-indent: -18pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt 21.3pt; mso-para-margin-left: 0gd; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: 7.1pt">
<font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'times new roman'"><span style="mso-list: ignore">-</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt">In the Birthrate Improving Idea Competition, Kim Bo-young won a grand prize for presenting the idea of operating the 24-hour hotline for pediatrician consultation and publishing a guidebook for emergency treatments. <o:p></o:p></span></font></font></p>
<p class="MsoListParagraph" style="text-indent: -18pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt 21.3pt; mso-para-margin-left: 0gd; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: 7.1pt">
<font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'times new roman'"><span style="mso-list: ignore">-</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt">In Pro-natal Slogan Competition, Oh Geum-na’s ‘Children are life-long presents to parents while brothers and sisters are life-long friends to each other’ was selected as the best, whereas Kim Jae-wook’s UCC titled ‘Creation’ received the grand prize in UCC Competition. <o:p></o:p></span></font></font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent: -7.1pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt 7.1pt; mso-char-indent-count: -.59">
<span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt"><o:p><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman"> </font></o:p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt">
<span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt"><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000">In his speech celebrating the population day, the Health and Welfare Minister Moon Hyung-pyo pointed out that fertility incentives and enhanced support for child caring alone cannot fundamentally reverse the trend of low birthrate and said, “We need to shift our focus of pro-natal policy paradigm toward families and children and seriously consider the population crisis in a greater context of national management, including economic and social policies.”<o:p></o:p></font></font></span></p>
<p class="MsoListParagraph" style="text-indent: -18pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt 21.3pt; mso-para-margin-left: 0gd; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2">
<font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'times new roman'"><span style="mso-list: ignore">-<span style="font: 7pt 'times new roman'">          </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt">Minister Moon noted that with this sense of crisis, the Presidential Committee on Aging Society and Population Policy will discuss supplementary policies with regard to low birthrate. <o:p></o:p></span></font></font></p>
<p class="MsoListParagraph" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt 21.3pt; mso-para-margin-left: 0gd">
<span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt"><o:p><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman"> </font></o:p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt">
<span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt"><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000">An official at the Ministry of Health and Welfare said, “The 3rd Population Day Ceremony needs not to end as a mere ceremony but to serve as an opportunity to deepen our understanding of the implication of population crisis.” <o:p></o:p></font></font></span></p>
<p class="MsoListParagraph" style="text-indent: -18pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt 14.2pt; mso-para-margin-left: 0gd; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2">
<font color="#000000"><font face="Times New Roman"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'times new roman'"><span style="mso-list: ignore">-<span style="font: 7pt 'times new roman'">          </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt">He also noted the importance of building social trust and hope for the future in order to ensure that the society changes in a way conducive to marriage, reproduction and child bearing. <o:p></o:p></span></font></font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt">
<span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt"><o:p><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman"> </font></o:p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt">
<span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt"><font color="#000000"><font face="Times New Roman">In the second part of the ceremony, a symposium titled ‘Creating a Pro-Natal Culture and Setting the Direction of Population Education to Improve Public Perception’ will be held. <o:p></o:p></font></font></span></p>
<p>
<span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 107%; font-family: 'times new roman', 'serif'; font-size: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: '¸¼Àº °íµñ'; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-fareast; mso-ansi-language: en-us; mso-fareast-language: ko; mso-bidi-language: ar-sa"><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman">In addition, a variety of performances and events to improve the public perception of low birthrate will be held at Hangang Parks on July 12<sup>th</sup>.</font></span></p></td>
</tr>
